    "body": "This would make it a lot easier to work with classes and functions that have lots of arguments and properties.\r\nWhat I'm suggesting would look something like this.\r\nmodule.pyx\r\ncdef class example:\r\n cdef int a,b\r\n cpdef get_ints(self):\r\n  return (self.a, self.b)\r\n\r\nmodule.pxd\r\ncdef class example\r\n\r\nothermodule.pyx\r\nfrom module cimport example\r\ncdef example x=example()\r\nex.a=20\r\nx.b=40\r\nprint(x.get_ints())\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis way, the declaration is taken from one file, nothing has to be changed in two places.\r\nWhat could also work is adding a new decorator, which allows cimporting of whatever it's used on.\r\nFor example:\r\nimport cython\r\n@cython.export\r\ncdef class example:\r\n int a,b\r\n\r\nThis would allow cimporting the example class without a .pyx file.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
